{"id":13414,"date":"2018-12-12T14:22:34","date_gmt":"2018-12-12T08:52:34","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=13414"},"modified":"2023-06-15T09:33:12","modified_gmt":"2023-06-15T04:03:12","slug":"shaktikanta-das","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/","title":{"rendered":"Shaktikanta Das Wiki, Age, Wife, Caste, Education, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-13423\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das.jpg\" alt=\"Shaktikanta Das\" width=\"627\" height=\"418\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 627px) 100vw, 627px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Shaktikanta Das is a <strong>retired IAS officer<\/strong> of Tamil Nadu Cadre. He has been one of the most prominent bureaucrats in the Ministry of Finance. Mr. Das has diverse experience in formulating financial policies; as he has served the Government of India for more than three decades, especially in the Ministry of Finance and the Department of Economic Affairs. In December 2018,\u00a0Shaktikanta Das became a household name when he was appointed the <strong>25th Governor of Reserve Bank of India (RBI)<\/strong>.\u00a0Let\u2019s delve into details about Shaktikanta Das\u2019s family, career, controversies, and more.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce32e9b8b9\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce32e9b8b9\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/#BiographyWiki\" title=\"Biography\/Wiki\">Biography\/Wiki<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/#Family_Caste\" title=\"Family &amp; Caste\">Family &amp; Caste<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/#Signature\" title=\"Signature\">Signature<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/#Education_Career\" title=\"Education &amp; Career\">Education &amp; Career<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/#Major_Designations\" title=\"Major Designations\">Major Designations<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/#Controversies\" title=\"Controversies\">Controversies<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/shaktikanta-das\/#Facts\" title=\"Facts\">Facts<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"BiographyWiki\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Biography\/Wiki<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Shaktikanta Das was born into a modest family of Bhubaneshwar, Odisha on\u00a026 February 1957 (<strong>aged 61; as in 2018<\/strong>). He is an alumnus of\u00a0Demonstration Multipurpose School, Bhubaneswar. He was considered <strong>a brilliant student<\/strong>\u00a0throughout his student life.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_13425\" style=\"width: 687px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-School-Demonstration-Multipurpose-School-In-Odisha.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13425\" class=\"wp-image-13425\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-School-Demonstration-Multipurpose-School-In-Odisha.jpg\" alt=\"Shaktikanta Das School Demonstration Multipurpose School In Odisha\" width=\"677\" height=\"254\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-School-Demonstration-Multipurpose-School-In-Odisha.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-School-Demonstration-Multipurpose-School-In-Odisha-300x113.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-School-Demonstration-Multipurpose-School-In-Odisha-768x288.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 677px) 100vw, 677px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-13425\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Shaktikanta Das School Demonstration Multipurpose School In Odisha<\/p><\/div>\n<p>After completing his schooling from Odisha, he moved to Delhi; where he pursued his graduation and <strong>post graduation in History<\/strong> from the\u00a0St. Stephen&#8217;s College, University of Delhi.<\/p>\n<div class=\"flex-video flex-video-youtube\"><iframe title=\"Shaktikanta Das Biography\" width=\"1060\" height=\"596\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/m-AWV87v41s?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family_Caste\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Family &amp; Caste<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>There is not much information about his family. His marital status is also not available.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Signature\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Signature<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_13519\" style=\"width: 584px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13519\" class=\" wp-image-13519\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Signature.jpg\" alt=\"Shaktikanta Das Signature\" width=\"574\" height=\"365\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Signature.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Signature-300x191.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Signature-768x489.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 574px) 100vw, 574px\" \/><p id=\"caption-attachment-13519\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Shaktikanta Das Signature<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Education_Career\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Education &amp; Career<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Shaktikanta Das has more than <strong>three decades of experience as an IAS Officer<\/strong>. After passing the Civil Services Examination,\u00a0Shaktikanta Das&#8217; first posting was as an\u00a0Assistant Collector in 1982. Thereafter, he went on serving the Government of India in various capacities including-\u00a0Secretary in the Ministry of Chemicals &amp; Fertilizers (2013-14),\u00a0Secretary in the Ministry of Finance Department of Revenue (2014-15), and Secretary in the Ministry of Finance Department of Economic Affairs (2015-2017). Even after his <strong>retirement from the IAS in 2017<\/strong>, he was appointed as <strong>a member of the 15th Finance Commission<\/strong>. On 11 December 2018, he was appointed the 25th Governor of Reserve Bank of India; after the resignation of <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/urjit-patel\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Urjit Patel<\/a>.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_13447\" style=\"width: 568px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-new-RBI-governor.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13447\" class=\"wp-image-13447\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-new-RBI-governor.jpg\" alt=\"Shaktikanta Das In A Meeting\" width=\"558\" height=\"289\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-new-RBI-governor.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-new-RBI-governor-300x155.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-new-RBI-governor-768x397.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-13447\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Shaktikanta Das In A Meeting<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Major_Designations\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Major Designations<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Secretary Industries Department (2006)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Special Commissioner Additional Secretary Revenue (2007-08)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Joint Secretary Ministry of Finance Department of Expenditure (2008-09)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Joint Secretary Ministry of Finance Department of Economic Affairs (2009-11)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Additional Secretary Ministry of Finance Department of Economic Affairs (2011-13)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Special Secretary Ministry of Finance Department of Economic Affairs (2013)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Secretary Ministry of Chemicals &amp; Fertilizers (2013-14)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Secretary Ministry of Finance Department of Revenue (2014-15)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Secretary Ministry of Finance Department of Economic Affairs (2015-2017)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>A Member of the Fifteenth Finance Commission (2017)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Governor of Reserve Bank of India (appointed on 11 December 2018)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Controversies\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Controversies<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>His appointment as the Governor of RBI was <strong>criticized<\/strong> by many on the pretext of his <strong>educational qualification;<\/strong> that being a student of History how he would deal with the financial policies.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 2016, he was criticised for his alleged involvement in the allotment of land to the U. S. firm <strong>Sanmina SCI Corporation<\/strong> at a concessional price in 2007, while he was serving in the Tamil Nadu state government.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Facts\"><\/span><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Facts<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Shaktikanta Das knows multiple languages including Odiya, Tamil, Hindi, and English.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He has more than three decades of experience as an IAS officer.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He was appointed as <strong>India&#8217;s Sherpa<\/strong> to the\u00a0<strong>G20 summit,<\/strong> held in Hamburg in July 2017.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Even though he was a student of History, he has dealt mainly with economics and finance throughout his career.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>He launched the new Indian currency notes along with Urjit Patel; after the <strong>demonetisation<\/strong> of\u00a0\u20b9500 and\u00a0\u20b91000 currency notes.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_13426\" style=\"width: 496px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Launching-New-Currency-Notes.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-13426\" class=\"wp-image-13426\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Launching-New-Currency-Notes.jpg\" alt=\"Shaktikanta Das Launching New Currency Notes\" width=\"486\" height=\"304\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Launching-New-Currency-Notes.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Launching-New-Currency-Notes-300x188.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-Launching-New-Currency-Notes-768x480.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 486px) 100vw, 486px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-13426\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Shaktikanta Das with Urjit Patel launching new currency notes<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>His hobbies include reading and writing.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In June 2023, he received the Governor of the Year Award by Central Banking in London.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_171090\" style=\"width: 352px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-with-his-award.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-171090\" class=\" wp-image-171090\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-with-his-award.jpg\" alt=\"Shaktikanta Das with his award\" width=\"342\" height=\"465\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-with-his-award.jpg 368w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/12\/Shaktikanta-Das-with-his-award-221x300.jpg 221w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 342px) 100vw, 342px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-171090\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Shaktikanta Das with his award<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Shaktikanta Das is a retired IAS officer of Tamil Nadu Cadre. He has been one of the most prominent bureaucrats in the Ministry of Finance. Mr. Das has diverse experience in formulating financial policies; as he has served the Government of India for more than three decades, especially in the Ministry of Finance and the Department of Economic Affairs. In December 2018,\u00a0Shaktikanta Das became a household name when he was appointed the 25th Governor of Reserve Bank of India (RBI).\u00a0Let\u2019s delve into details about Shaktikanta Das\u2019s family, career, controversies, and more. Biography\/Wiki Shaktikanta Das was born into a modest family <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":26,"featured_media":13423,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[2],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13414"}],"collection":[{"href":"h